fields.name: Laura Williams
fields.bio: Founder of Teifi TKD Laura undertook TKD at the age of 8 to help deal with bullies. Her passion continued through University obtaining her degree and 2nd dan in the same month. Reconnecting with her friend and sparring partner, Coach Holly, saw the formation of Teifi Takewondo

fields.name: Holly White
fields.bio: Holly started Taekwondo with school friend Coach Laura however due to her University degree temporarily stopped and began her journey in kickboxing. Returning home she reconnected with Laura to complete her first dan in takewondo whilst also introducing Laura to kickboxing fighting her way to her black belt.

fields.name: Adam Knight
fields.bio: Adam joined Teifi Taekwondo after relocating due to a change of career bringing with him knowledge and experience in Judo. Adam's dedication to learning saw him quickly rise through the ranks and his Judo expertise assisting the club in our self-defence drills across the classes.

fields.name: Emma Owen
fields.awards: Training for 1st Degree Black Belt Kickboxing
fields.bio: Emma is our first Junior to become an instructor moving up the ranks from Student to Teacher. Which is good for a primary school teacher, those PE Lessons must be fun. Emma take our Tigers and Juniors before training herself with both the seniors and ladies classes, and has even joined Holly and Laura in Kickboxing too.

fields.name: Blitz Dipped Foam Gloves
fields.description: Moulded to fit securely to the knuckles with an elastic Velcro wrap strap around the wrist. Lightweight and compact, the special dipped foam material absorbs blows, knocks and impact. Ideal for young students. Made from soft EVA foam, dipped in a PVC resin, and vacuum moulded to finish. Easy to wipe clean before and after use.

fields.name: Blitz Semi Contact Open Palm Gloves
fields.description: Made from Nama Hide™ Leather, this semi contact open palm glove is specifically designed for semi contact, full contact or bag work. Used in clubs across the UK, this glove includes an adjustable, elasticated, Velcro strap for perfect fit and comfort. Easy to wipe clean before and after use

fields.name: Blitz Dipped Foam Foot Guards
fields.description: The shock absorbing foam foot guards offer great protection during kicking techniques. Made from a soft EVA foam dipped in PVC resin, and vacuum moulded to finish, the foot guards are contoured to cover the majority of the foot, with cut-outs around the achilles and instep for ease of movement. The tongue and heel of the guards feature ventilation holes for air flow and to prevent moisture build-up, keeping the wearer cool. The elasticated Velcro wrap-around strap provides a secure and comfortable fit. The bottom of the foot guard also includes two reinforced elasticated straps to hold the foot in place and, open areas at the heel, ball of the foot and toes for a solid grip on flooring. Easy to wipe clean before and after use.

fields.name: Blitz Semi Contact Foot Protectors
fields.description: Made from tough, anti-slip Nama Hide™ Leather, this semi contact foot protector is specifically designed for Teifi Taekwondo’s teachings. A wrap-around Velcro strap at the back and elastic strap underneath improves comfort and fit to enhance performance. Easy to wipe clean before and after use.

fields.name: Blitz Dipped Foam Shin Guards
fields.description: The shock absorbing foam shin guards offer the ultimate protection when sparring. Made from a soft EVA foam dipped in PVC resin, and vacuum moulded to finish, the guards are contoured to cover the majority of the shin. The front of the shin features ventilation holes for air flow and to prevent moisture build-up, keeping the wearer cool. Securely fastens with two elasticated wrap-around Velcro fastenings for a comfortable fit. Easy to wipe clean before and after use.

fields.name: Blitz Fusion Shin Guards
fields.description: Blitz Fusion Shin Guards provide the ultimate shock absorption against the hardest impact and a rapid recovery after use. The high density foam, with additional padding on the shin, features a non-abrasive inner lining that mould perfectly to your shin for extreme comfort. The two adjustable Velcro straps to the back of the shin guards allow for a secure and precise fit, keeping them firmly in place without any movement. Nama Hide™ Leather, that's easy to wipe clean before and after use.

fields.name: Blitz Dipped Head Guard
fields.description: The shock absorbing foam head guard is designed to absorb high impact blows to the forehead, ears and rear of the head when sparring. The head guard is specifically shaped to reduce uncomfortable neck pressure at the back and includes ear guards for the ultimate protection. Made from a soft EVA foam dipped in PVC resin, and vacuum moulded to finish, the head guard also features ventilation holes for air flow and to prevent moisture build-up, keeping the wearer cool. Securely fastens with an elastic Velcro strap under the chin for a comfortable and easy adjustable fit. Easy to wipe clean before and after use.

fields.name: Blitz Club Semi Contact Head Guard
fields.description: Constructed from Nama Hide™ Leather, this semi contact head guard includes a Velcro cross design fastening on top of the head and a Velcro strap under the chin for a compact, comfortable and precise fit. Ear sections are bound, safeguarding your ears. A breathable, moisture absorbing, anti-microbial lining is also included to retain freshness. Easy to wipe clean before and after use. Latex free.

fields.title: Welcome to the New Website for Teifi Taekwondo.
fields.body:
Welcome to Teifi Taekwondo.co.uk

Since the return to in person training post Pandemic. We’ve spent the last few years of blending digital training during lockdowns, to socially distanced sessions outdoors and a brief return to in house sessions as lockdowns ended as guidance changed.The website contains all our class information alongside our Shop and Blog.

Firstly the shop. To help us keep everything running smoothly everyone will be asked to purchase sessions for the month from our Shiny New Digital Shop - this will cut down on the money being handled in class (and should effectively save time between sessions resulting in more time training.)

Other products are also available and will be collected prior your next training session at the hall. this is also the opportunity you will have to pick your colours for Kit purchased through us. (Remember You don’t have to buy your Sparring kit through us.)

Secondly The Blog. We know keeping up to date with the information given in sessions is hard (particularly as parents of children who don’t exactly remember everything our instructors say.) We will therefore make announcements concerning the club in the blog and they will be there for all to see.

Have fun! You Got this!

Laura, Holly, Adam and Emma.

fields.title: Upcoming Grading
fields.body:
It that time of the year our First in Person grading since our full Time return to the hall.

Dates:
Coloured Belts (Junior Members) 4 . 12 . 2021
Coloured Belts (Seniors including Ladies) 4 .12 . 2021
Black Belt Grading 5 . 12 . 2021

Times will be confirmed closer to the dates

That means we are 5 WEEKS From Gradings

Instructors will invite you to test in the coming sessions, at that point you will need to ensure your membership is valid and purchase your grading from the Shop.

See you in the Dojang
You Got this
Holly

PS Laura is away this week - SO I will be running training whilst Laura is away. I look forward to getting to see our Tigers in action… I normally don’t get to train you guys… Or assist Emma :)

fields.title: Two Weeks Till Gradings
fields.body:
Hi Guys

We are just 2 weeks away from gradings.
Here is the planned timetable for grading Weekend

Juniors - Coloured Belts - 10am - 12pm (Please arrive at 9:30 for Registration and Warm up)
Seniors inc Ladies - Coloured Belts - 2pm - 5pm (Please arrive at 1:30 for Registration and Warm up)
Your session is longer as we want to see what we know you can do.

Black Belt - SUNDAY. 2pm - 6pm (Please arrive at 1:30 for Registration and Warm up)
Juniors and Seniors will Grade together.

Grading Checklist:

  • Valid Membership
  • Grading Session Purchased from Shop
  • Teifi Takewondo Passport (Book included with Initial membership)
  • Clean Dobok
  • Sparring Equipment
  • Waterbottle

We’re close- and you wouldn’t have been invited to grade had your instructors not believed you were ready to test.

See you in the Dojang
You Got this
Laura & Holly

fields.title: Tigers Grading
fields.body:
Cubs We've not forgotten about you Our Tigers will grade in session (in the fun ways) following our grading weekend. -Week of December 6th
All information will be given to parents this week (Theory information)
Keep Fighting
Laura & Emma

fields.title: Christmas Party and Awards Event
fields.body:
The Coaches have been thinking.
With gradings on the 4th and 5th (Tigers during the week of the 6th) we want to go out of the year on a high note

Tigers Christmas party - Saturday December 11th @ 1pm - 3pm
Juniors Christmas party - Saturday December 11th @ 3pm - 6pm
This will include

  • Inflatables
  • Hot Dogs
  • Awards for the Year (every child will receive an award.)
  • Games
  • Visit from a special guest

Parents will be asked to stay- and as most are members- we will have a parental challenge planned on one of our inflatables - after the coaching team have playfully waged war with one another

Seniors Christmas party - Will be arranged post classes (Ladies included) this week with Seniors, as we have a range of ages in class and we want to make sure everyone is involved.

fields.title: Grading Weekend!
fields.body:
It's Grading Weekend

We know you guys can do it. We’ve seen you all grow in confidence and develop your skills and understanding of Taekwondo over the last several months.

You wouldn't have been invited to grade if the instructors didn’t know you would soar through the tests with flying colours.

Tomorrow (or Sunday)
Relax
Give it your best

Good Luck Everyone
Laura, Holly, Adam and Emma.

fields.title: WELL DONE EVERYONE
fields.body:
What a Busy weekend

Congratulations to all our new belts.
You all soared like we knew you would.

Big shout out to the Ladies who stepped up and showed the Men in the senior class what it was like to 'fight like a girl' - Remember You are allowed to join in with the senior class whenever you want if you wish to do so - I'm positive the ladies who are already there and don't attend the or ladies only classes want to meet you on the mats again, and some of the men want to understand your approach to sparring.

We look forward to seeing new colours and stripes fill the hall this week

Wear your new colours with pride.

Tigers your chance to roar comes soon- We have your patches and stripes waiting for you.

See You in the Dojang
Your Proud Instructor Team

fields.title: In House Competition?
fields.body:
With gradings done the instructor team have a question, and would like some input...

How would you guys like to participate in an in-house Competition?

We would like to run a variety of competitions over one weekend. This includes at least both Forms and Sparring for Juniors and Senior sections.
But in order to do this we want to know that members would want to “compete”.
Sections would be split by grades, ages and gender- Ladies of the Ladies Classes and those in the senior classes would compete against each other
The focus being members get to practice for tournaments outside of the club, whilst being in a safe environment with people they train and spar with on a regular basis.

We’ve also thought EVERY competitor, both Junior and Senior will receive a medal for competing that weekend. Competing (especially sparring for points not practice) is scary and everyone deserves to be rewarded for taking on the challenge.

Our Tigers would have a separate “sports day” with us focused on showcasing and developing their skills... With Medals and Specially Designed Patches up for grabs!

If this Interests you please inform any one of the instructor team.

See You In the Dojang
Laura, Holly, Adam & Emma

fields.title: Nadolig Llawen
fields.body:
Nadolig Llawen a Blwyddyn Newydd Dda
Merry Christmas and A Happy New Year
즐거운 성탄절 보내시고 새해 복 많이 받으세요

We want to thank all members and parents for the har work and dedication you have given us during the last 12 months. Returning to us for outdoor sessions and then back to the hall in the Autumn has been amazing and we (Myself, Holly, Adam and Emma) are eternally grateful for your commitment and support. Here's to 2022 and nothing major happening.

See You In The Dojang.... Classes Start Back Week Commencing January 10th 2022
Laura, Holly, Adam and Emma



P.S. Happy Birthday Holly - from everyone at the club.

fields.title: Competition Update
fields.body:
Hi Guys

The instructors have been blown away with the messages, conversations and enthusiasm we have had with and from members in junior, senior and ladies classes.
You guys want to compete

So we WILL be having an in-house tournament.
There will be two competitions

  • Forms
  • Sparring
Entry Forms will be created and distributed once we have finalised a date.

I (Holly) will be over seeing the organisation of it- So Laura can keep the club and classes running smoothly.

Catch you in the Dojang
Holly
